1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:08,008
[groovy music playing]

2
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:12,971
[McEnroe] Devi couldn't believe her eyes.

3
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,349
Her brand new friend,
whom she just decided to like,

4
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:19,519
was stone-cold flirting
with Ben freaking Gross.

5
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:21,021
-[Ben] Oh!
-Excuse me!

6
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,355
[McEnroe] Pencil games?

7
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:24,983
Why don't they just go at it
on the lab table?

8
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:28,486
What happened to the Aneesa
who put Ben in his place the other night?

9
00:00:28,570 --> 00:00:33,158
As Devi thought back on that interaction,
it looked a little different to her.

10
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:36,786
Since you're new, you should know
you're hanging out with a social grenade.

11
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:38,288
[Aneesa laughs]

12
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:41,249
Yeah, I'm not gonna take social advice

13
00:00:41,332 --> 00:00:45,420
from a guy who looks like he still
gets his hair cut by a children's barber.

14
00:00:45,503 --> 00:00:46,921
[whimsical music playing]

15
00:00:47,005 --> 00:00:50,216
[McEnroe] Mother of Borg!
That's some sexual tension.

16
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:55,263
And was that a goddamn Beyoncé hair-flip?
How had Devi been so blind?

17
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,390
[laughs]

18
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:59,017
[teacher] Okay, agents.

19
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:02,771
Get your spy glasses on
because today we'll be learning about…

20
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:04,397
bonds.

21
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:06,566
Covalent bonds.

22
00:01:07,192 --> 00:01:11,488
[McEnroe] No, we won't, Mrs. Paloma,
because this bond was broken.

23
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:13,531
[techno music playing]

24
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:20,455
Then she did a crazy Beyoncé hair-flip.

25
00:01:20,538 --> 00:01:23,041
[scoffs] And she didn't even
shower him with dandruff!

26
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:26,086
Devi, you're holding that pen
like a knife again.

27
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,796
Oh yeah, my b.

28
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:31,549
It's just… Does she not know girl code?
You don't flirt with your friend's ex!

29
00:01:32,175 --> 00:01:33,760
Did you tell her he's your ex?

30
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:37,097
No, but she should be able to sense it.
Our chemistry is palpable.

31
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:40,141
So you still have feelings for Ben.

32
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:43,061
I should've picked Ben in the first place!
He was all in.

33
00:01:43,144 --> 00:01:44,395
I got greedy, Doc.

34
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:47,440
Now my hands are covered
in the crumbs of my failed relationships.

35
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:49,400
[laughing] Oh hell, Devi.

36
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:51,778
I am so glad to have you back,

37
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:54,531
but I'm gonna need time-and-a-half
for these sessions.

38
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:58,701
I know I really hurt Ben, but deep down,
I still think there's hope for us.

39
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:01,746
Well, I thought you said
that he would never forgive you.

40
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:05,166
Yeah, but full-blown hatred
is kind of a comfortable place for us.

41
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:06,626
We've done that 180 before.

42
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:09,587
But not if Aneesa
keeps grabbing his goddamn pencil.

43
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:13,842
Is that a euphemism?
Uh, I don't even wanna know.

44
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:17,679
Devi, regardless of what happens
between you and Ben,

45
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:20,974
I think we need to work
on your approach to stress.

46
00:02:21,057 --> 00:02:24,894
Perhaps, introduce some techniques
that would help you avoid--

47
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:27,021
Losing my shit? Okay. Okay.

48
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:30,316
What are we thinking? Meditation? Candles?

49
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:34,028
[gasps] Could you prescribe me weed?
Or is that like only for real doctors?

50
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:35,363
Watch it.

51
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:37,782
Right. I'm thinking something more simple.

52
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:42,412
Like, when you feel
that surge of anger coming up, stop…

53
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:46,124
[inhales deeply] …take a deep breath,
and listen to some soothing music

54
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:48,835
or anything that'll bring you peace.

55
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:51,504
-I think weed would be more effective.
-No.

56
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,756
Fine, I'll try it.

57
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,468
[McEnroe] Dr. Ryan
was a bit of a know-it-all,

58
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,179
but maybe she had a point.

59
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:00,638
Maybe it was possible

60
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:03,391
to handle stressful situations
in a mature, rational--

61
00:03:03,474 --> 00:03:04,642
What up, dude?

62
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:06,644
-Aah!
-Whoa, are you okay?

63
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:08,688
[McEnroe] As if you care, Aneesa!

64
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,607
Nope. Bad McEnroe. Bad!

65
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:13,026
Yep! I'm fine.

66
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:15,778
I was just, um, remembering an article

67
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:18,573
about how we all swallow
at least 20 spiders while we sleep.

68
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:20,408
That's been debunked.

69
00:03:20,491 --> 00:03:22,702
Speaking of swallowing stuff…

70
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:27,290
Not sexual. Let me finish!
Also, not sexual.

71
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:29,250
My mom made some of her signature fudgies.

72
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:31,336
But are they sexual?

73
00:03:31,419 --> 00:03:34,047
[McEnroe] Damn it!
Devi was gonna make the same joke.

74
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:37,008
Except, it was longer and less funny.

75
00:03:37,091 --> 00:03:39,928
So why'd your mom make the brownies?
What's the occashe?

76
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:43,014
She made them for Eve,
but Eve is vegan, gluten-free,

77
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:46,351
and thinks that M&amp;M's are complicit
in the corporatization of America.

78
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:48,353
It's like my mom doesn't even know her.

79
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:50,271
Well, have you introduced them?

80
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:53,149
Oh no, no. Are you kidding me?
Eve can't meet my mom.

81
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:55,944
Why? I thought your mom's
supportive of your relationship.

82
00:03:56,027 --> 00:03:58,112
Yeah, too supportive.

83
00:03:58,196 --> 00:04:01,741
She's trying so hard to be an ally,
but she keeps saying the wrong thing.

84
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:05,453
Like yesterday, she asked me if I wanted
to get a funky, lesbian haircut.

85
00:04:05,536 --> 00:04:07,038
-[whirring]
-Oh, queen.

86
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:08,706
Yeah, that's not great.

87
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:10,792
Hey, at least you're allowed to date.

88
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:14,504
My mom covered my eyes during the kiss
in Lady and the Tramp

89
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:16,256
so I wouldn't get any ideas.

90
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:19,968
[McEnroe] But it seems as though
you have gotten some ideas, Aneesa.

91
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:23,221
And we all know who your spaghetti-dog is.

92
00:04:24,472 --> 00:04:27,016
[mouthful] And stop being
such an elegant eater!

93
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,937
Devi, there you are.
May I talk to you for a moment?

94
00:04:31,437 --> 00:04:32,981
So it's come to my attention

95
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:35,775
that you have been skipping PE
for several weeks.

96
00:04:35,858 --> 00:04:39,612
Right. I was told that my credits weren't
gonna count at my high school in India,

97
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:41,364
so I figured, "What's the point?"

98
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:45,868
Since you're no longer moving to India,
that credit very much does count.

99
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:48,997
I see. So where am I at? A "B"?

100
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,540
[scoffs] A "B-plus"?

101
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,250
-No, you're getting an "F."
-[screams]

102
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,961
Okay. [chuckles] Now, let's just relax.

103
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:59,090
Coach Noble has agreed
to bump up your grade if you participate

104
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:04,220
in my cross country team's
24-hour relay for charity. [chuckles]

105
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:07,974
Ugh! Can't I write an essay about
the history of track and field instead?

106
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:09,726
No. Nobody wants to read that.

107
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:12,562
You just get a team together.
You're doing the relay.

108
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:15,648
[school bell ringing]

109
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:18,651
Hey, I have a weird request.

110
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,653
We'll be on your team.
We heard everything.

111
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:22,363
You only walked like two feet away.

112
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:24,699
-I'll ask you Eve too!
-Cool, I'll text Eleanor.

113
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:28,119
Oh, she's out.
She has extra Glass Menagerie rehearsals.

114
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:32,540
Shit. What other friends do we have?
Should we ask the lunch ladies?

115
00:05:32,623 --> 00:05:34,542
I could ask some of my robotics peeps.

116
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:35,585
Oh, wait, let's--

117
00:05:35,668 --> 00:05:38,504
Hey, Eric! Do you wanna join
our 24-hour relay team?

118
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:40,131
Hell, yes, I do!

119
00:05:40,214 --> 00:05:43,217
Me and my real human girlfriend
will be there.

120
00:05:43,301 --> 00:05:46,429
Okay! Well, that's me and Eve,
Eric and Rosalia,

121
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:48,389
Devi, Aneesa.

122
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:49,849
Who else should we invite?

123
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:50,850
What about Ben?

124
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:53,102
[McEnroe] And boom goes the dynamite.

125
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:55,104
We had fun with him
the other night, right?

126
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:57,398
Yes, we did.

127
00:05:58,024 --> 00:06:00,401
You should totally, totally text him.

128
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:03,029
Now if you'll excuse me, I'm just gonna…

129
00:06:03,821 --> 00:06:05,073
go over here.

130
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:08,993
[pants]

131
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:11,996
[McEnroe] As Devi felt
the rage building up inside her,

132
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,290
she remembered Dr. Ryan's advice,

133
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:18,127
and decided to listen to something
soothing that could calm her down.

134
00:06:19,045 --> 00:06:20,505
[Mohan] Uh, hi, it's Dad.

135
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:22,632
Um, I'm here at the mall to pick you up.

136
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,717
Uh, I'm parked in front of P.F. Chang's,

137
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:28,346
but a brute security guard
is making me circle around.

138
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:32,558
Oh, wait, I see you.
Ah, there's my perfect girl.

139
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:35,144
[doorbell rings]

140
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:39,315
Nope, not interested in joining
whatever cult this is. Thank you.

141
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,525
No, no, worry not!

142
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:44,028
We are from Kamala's lab.
I am Evan. This is Setseg.

143
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:46,364
We're here to pick her up
for the video game convention.

144
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,116
Right. Okay.

145
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,201
Why don't you wait right there?

146
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:52,912
And if you don't mind,
please take off your shoes.

147
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:55,998
I'm afraid that's not possible.
My shoes are connected to my pants.

148
00:06:56,082 --> 00:07:00,128
My shoes are not connected to my pants,
but you do not want me to take them off.

149
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:02,004
Right, okay, yeah.

150
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:05,800
Kamala, y-your friends are here, ma!

151
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,428
Technically, we're her bosses,
thank you very much.

152
00:07:09,053 --> 00:07:11,514
So how much did this house cost?

153
00:07:11,597 --> 00:07:12,974
[footsteps approaching]

154
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:14,058
Holy shit!

155
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,440
[Nalini] Ayyo.

156
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:24,402
[in Tamil] Why do you look like
a sexy flight attendant from Mars?

157
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:27,113
[in Tamil] I have to dress this way
to get respected in my work.

158
00:07:27,738 --> 00:07:30,867
[in English] It was the least suggestive
female character I could find.

159
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:33,744
We should skedaddle,
but it was a pleasure meeting all of you.

160
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:36,038
I enjoyed hearing you
speak your native tongue.

161
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:38,624
It is a beautiful, beautiful language.

162
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:41,294
Blessings upon your horns.
Setseg, the door.

163
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:42,879
-It's open.
-[Evan] I can see that.

164
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,383
This is so undignified.

165
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,010
I know.

166
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,304
[door closes]

167
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:56,309
Okay, mitoshondria.

168
00:07:56,392 --> 00:07:57,768
Mitochondria.

169
00:07:58,394 --> 00:07:59,854
-Right.
-Um… [sighs]

170
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,148
It's the powerhouse of the cell,

171
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:06,194
which turns nutrients
into chemical energy.

172
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,570
-Dude, you got it!
-Ha!

173
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:09,780
Hell, yeah! Suck it, science!

174
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:11,073
-[laughs]
-[Devi sniffs]

175
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,493
Did you just smell me?

176
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:15,703
-No.
-Okay.

177
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,332
I think we've done some good work today.
Should we take a break?

178
00:08:19,415 --> 00:08:21,250
Paxton, this is the first card.

179
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,212
You have 99 more terms left to learn
before your test on Monday.

180
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,506
Shit! School's so repetitive.

181
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:28,883
Why can't it be more like swimming?

182
00:08:30,176 --> 00:08:31,719
You dropped pencil.

183
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:34,013
Oh. Thanks.

184
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:36,307
-[giggles]
-[Devi] You know what?

185
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:39,602
Maybe it's healthy for you to learn
some things don't come so easy.

186
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:41,145
-Oh my God.
-[laughs] Move!

187
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,314
[McEnroe] Well, well, well. Who are they?

188
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:47,860
Doubles-partners Bob and Mike Bryan,
incapable of doing anything on their own?

189
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:50,905
Hey, Devi, Ben and I
are helping set up the 24-hour relay.

190
00:08:50,988 --> 00:08:54,867
Look who got a free badge
that says "volunteer"?

191
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:55,993
Ya bish! [laughs]

192
00:08:56,077 --> 00:09:00,748
Cool! Yeah, I used to be a Girl Scout,
so I have like hella badges at home.

193
00:09:01,707 --> 00:09:02,708
Cool.

194
00:09:02,792 --> 00:09:03,960
Aneesa, come on!

195
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:06,921
We gotta get there first so our tents
aren't next to the porta-potties.

196
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:08,881
All right. See you guys later.

197
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:14,053
Why is she so excited?
Who even wants to go to a 24-hour relay?

198
00:09:14,136 --> 00:09:16,430
I do? It rocks!

199
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:20,101
I mean, there's a reason everyone calls it
the 69-hour three-way. [chuckles]

200
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:22,186
-Say what?
-Everyone hooks up there.

201
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:25,731
I mean, I'd definitely go
if we didn't have to study all weekend.

202
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:29,902
Oh. Uh, about that. I kinda have to go.

203
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:32,822
Not to hook up! Just so I don't fail PE.

204
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:36,325
Wait, what? How am I supposed to learn
all this stuff without you?

205
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:38,578
You have the flashcards.
That's the hard part.

206
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,497
All you have to do is review them over
for three days straight.

207
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:43,082
That's the fun part.

208
00:09:43,874 --> 00:09:44,959
-[sighs]
-Yay.

209
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,919
[indistinct chatter]

210
00:09:47,003 --> 00:09:51,924
Hey! So since my mom is head chaperone,
she insisted on making us team shirts.

211
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,927
[Devi] "The Jodie Fasters."

212
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,470
Wow, you weren't kidding.

213
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:59,223
Oh, snap!
You decided to introduce her to Eve?

214
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,225
No. Why would you say that?

215
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:05,271
Damn, I forgot
they were both gonna be here!

216
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:07,440
[Devi] It doesn't seem like
they recognize each other.

217
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:10,109
Your lack of social media presence
has once again saved the day.

218
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:12,612
I'll have to spend the next 24 hours
trying to keep them apart.

219
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:15,489
Don't worry. Everyone's so consumed
with their own stuff

220
00:10:15,573 --> 00:10:18,743
that they forget to stop and notice
what's going on with other people.

221
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:22,204
Like for instance,
what's going on with Ben and Aneesa?

222
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:23,956
They seem kind of chummy, right?

223
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:28,377
Oh, you don't have to worry.
Aneesa is way out of Ben's league.

224
00:10:28,461 --> 00:10:31,339
Okay? She would never stoop that low.

225
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:35,176
-No offense.
-Facts. You're probably right.

226
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:39,347
And besides, this is an open field
surrounded by parents and teachers.

227
00:10:39,430 --> 00:10:40,806
Where would they even do it anyway?

228
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:44,977
Welcome to the Spurt Yurt!
Sign up to hook up.

229
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:48,147
Unless you're a teacher.
In that case, this is just a study hall.

230
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,274
Trent, what is this?

231
00:10:50,358 --> 00:10:53,069
It's a safe space to consensually rail.

232
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:56,572
It's kinda my modern take on the classic
Billy Wilder film, The Apartment.

233
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:58,366
I really tricked it out this year.

234
00:10:58,449 --> 00:10:59,659
[unzipping]

235
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:01,535
It's pretty sweet, huh?

236
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:04,705
My brother stole that soundproofing foam
when he got kicked out of his band.

237
00:11:04,789 --> 00:11:07,708
That means you can O as loud as you want.

238
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:10,086
