Are you embarrassed of me?

472
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:33,870
No, of course not! I'm embarrassed of her.

473
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:35,914
I know she's gonna say
something weird to you.

474
00:23:35,997 --> 00:23:38,834
She's definitely gonna tell you
how much she liked the movie Carol.

475
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:42,504
Great, I hope she does.
It's my favorite Christmas movie.

476
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:44,714
Now, suck it up and introduce us.

477
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:48,301
Fab. Haven't seen you for the whole relay.
Where've you been hiding?

478
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,178
Hi, Mom. Um…

479
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:53,223
This is Eve, my girlfriend.

480
00:23:53,306 --> 00:23:55,100
Eve? The Eve?

481
00:23:55,976 --> 00:23:59,479
Oh my gosh,
it is so nice to finally meet you!

482
00:23:59,563 --> 00:24:02,816
Did Fabiola tell you?
I hung a rainbow flag on our porch.

483
00:24:02,899 --> 00:24:05,777
That's awesome!
And also, great job on the relay.

484
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:07,404
Everything looks amazing.

485
00:24:07,487 --> 00:24:09,990
Aw! Well, if you think this looks good,

486
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:13,118
wait until you see what the PTA does
for the Winter Dance.

487
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:15,745
You two are going, right?

488
00:24:16,455 --> 00:24:18,498
I don't really think
that's our thing, Mom.

489
00:24:19,082 --> 00:24:21,001
Uh, it's the Winter Dance. [chuckles]

490
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:22,669
It's a tradition!

491
00:24:23,211 --> 00:24:25,505
It's where they crown
the Cricket King and Queen.

492
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:29,134
Mom, it's just a popularity contest
that's like super heteronormative

493
00:24:29,217 --> 00:24:31,303
and reinforces the gender binary.

494
00:24:31,803 --> 00:24:32,804
Right, Eve?

495
00:24:32,888 --> 00:24:36,475
Yeah, I don't know if anyone really cares
about Cricket King and Queen anymore.

496
00:24:36,558 --> 00:24:38,018
I was Cricket Queen.

497
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:39,853
Oh, I'm so sorry--

498
00:24:39,936 --> 00:24:42,272
And Fabiola's dad was Cricket King.

499
00:24:42,355 --> 00:24:45,025
We were actually
the first Cricket King and Queen of color.

500
00:24:45,108 --> 00:24:46,943
Whoa, that's amazing!

501
00:24:47,027 --> 00:24:49,488
And it may sound silly,
but it really meant a lot

502
00:24:49,571 --> 00:24:51,698
to all of the other students
who looked like us.

503
00:24:51,781 --> 00:24:53,241
Oh my God, Fab,

504
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:55,535
we should run for Cricket King and Queen!

505
00:24:55,619 --> 00:24:57,245
Cricket Queen and Queen.

506
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:59,456
That is an excellent idea. [chuckles]

507
00:24:59,539 --> 00:25:03,627
Is it too early to say, "Yas, Queens!"

508
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:06,254
-Mom, yes.
-[laughing] It's not too early at all.

509
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:07,964
Fab, your mom's so cool.

510
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:10,258
[Elise] Aw! I love Eve.

511
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:13,553
You should come to our house
and watch Carol sometime.

512
00:25:13,637 --> 00:25:15,055
-I love Carol.
-[Elise] Okay.

513
00:25:15,138 --> 00:25:17,349
So come with me because I wanted to talk…

514
00:25:17,432 --> 00:25:19,267
[gentle music playing]

515
00:25:22,270 --> 00:25:25,982
Hey, what happened to you?
Did you get attacked by another coyote?

516
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:27,067
I wish.

517
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,653
-Dr. Vishwakumar.
-Yes, Ms. Warner. How are you?

518
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:31,446
Well, everything is mediocre.

519
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:35,575
But listen, I just want to tell you
what a successful relay Devi had.

520
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:37,577
Not only did she do all of her laps,

521
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:41,164
but I saw her working extra hard
to get her teammates involved as well.

522
00:25:41,665 --> 00:25:44,084
Consider your PE grade changed to an "A."

523
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:47,295
Thank you. That's very nice of you.

524
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:48,630
You're welcome.

525
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:51,925
Well, well, young lady.

526
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:54,302
You should be proud of yourself.

527
00:25:54,386 --> 00:25:55,428
Shut the trunk.

528
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:57,597
[car door opens]

529
00:25:58,265 --> 00:25:59,307
[door beeps]

530
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:00,433
[car door closes]

531
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:07,357
[McEnroe]
Devi was far from proud of herself.

532
00:26:13,905 --> 00:26:17,576
[Mohan on voicemail] Uh, hi, it's Dad.
Um, I'm here at the mall to pick you up.

533
00:26:17,659 --> 00:26:20,161
Uh, I'm parked
in front of P.F. Chang's, but…

534
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,331
[softly] Is that her?

535
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:26,918
-No, it's the other one. The skinny one.
-Oh… Okay.

536
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:30,797
[McEnroe] The rumor had spread like
a wine stain on a pair of tennis whites.

537
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:33,675
Was that why
Aneesa wasn't at school today?

538
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:36,219
Devi couldn't imagine feeling any lower.

539
00:26:36,303 --> 00:26:39,598
[Ms. Warner on intercom] Devi Vishwakumar,
please report to the principal's office.

540
00:26:39,681 --> 00:26:40,974
[McEnroe] Until now.

541
